                        "type": "0",
                        "version": 0,
                        "content": "The client is being seen by the primary health care provider (PHCP). During the visit, the client states that being a single parent who works is stressful, and because of this, feels chronically fatigued. The client also states feeling anxious because the client cannot find consistent day care for the child. The nurse wants to help the client with community resources. Which resource would be best for the client?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "80db17ea97ed8fdcd1b6b9666390fca1",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Applying 应用",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nAccess to community organizations and resources can help alleviate some burdens the single parent may encounter. Services such as child care, wellness clinics for access to screenings, and employment opportunities can set the single parent up for success. There are no data in the question indicating that the client needs the names of food banks or the names of psychologists. Although the client is chronically fatigued, there are no data indicating a sleep study is warranted.\n\nTest-Taking Strategy:\nNote the strategic word, best. You are looking for the option that addresses the data in the question most directly. Using the data in the question, identify the client's primary problem, that the client cannot find consistent day care for the child. A community resource the nurse can help with is giving the client a list of names of child care facilities to help alleviate the burden of inconsistent child care.",
